      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is the jurisprudential approach that insists the Constitution must be interpreted according to the meaning it had at the time it was ratified. Proponents argue this prevents unelected judges from imposing their personal, ever-changing policy preferences onto the law. By adhering to the original public meaning, originalism ensures the Constitution remains a fixed, stable document reflecting the will of the founders. This approach is fundamentally rooted in respecting democratic processes over judicial activism.",
